{
  "texts": [
    "By contrast, CAPs can diffuse faster in lattices with higher ϕ (Fig. 5a, b).",
    "Note that when the obstacle lattice is imperfect, interesting transport phenomena may emerge.",
    "For example, if an obstacle lattice consists of two different lattices with different diffusivities, particles will exhibit topotaxis effect by migrating into lower-diffusivity region 10, 47.",
    "Our additional simulations demonstrate that topotaxis effect is also present for CAPs moving in a binary lattice with identical packing fraction (Fig. S7).",
    "If a single lattice of obstacles is subject to a noisy configuration, CAP diffusivity will deviate from that of the reference perfect lattice; more details are provided in SI (Fig. S8)."
  ]
}